values: FINALLY saw Pirates of the Caribbean 2 Saturday.  Loved it!  Yummy yummy delicious.  So many pretty men.  Totally melted for Johnny Depp.  Those dark chocolate eyes.  Gah.  Drool.  Really want to see it again.

I have a new niece or nephew on the way! (I'm hoping boy) I have made a blanket for the last two, so I guess I really ought to make one for the new one as well. I'm thinking knit. I'm thinking very soft. I'm thinking maybe this: Very cute and I love the color choices. Orange is my favorite ya know. Now to find the right yarn and, gosh darn it, the freaking time.

1) Watch first season and maybe second of Entourage over again.  And marvel at Jeremy Piven's <strike>loveliness</strike> amazing acting abilities.  And Adrian Grenier's <strike>beauty</strike> er, talent as well.  
2) Read more War and Peace.  Hopefully.
3) Watch the last episode of Bones again.  Looooove me some David B!
4) Watch the model/sex episode of House that TiVo taped Tuesday, missed it the first time it aired at this past Tuesday.
5) Deposit kiddo at g'parent's to make this happen! Woot! 

Not too ambitious.  Not at all.

I really should use this journal more.   I have so many rabid obsession now, House, Bones, Entourage, Pride and Prejudice (and Pride & Prejudice, but don't tell the Firth lovers), Pirates of the Carribean, Superman, Fables, and on and on and on and on.  I don't like to post about it on my main blog so I really ought to do it here.  Lord knows, I wish I had someone to talk these things over with.  The hubby just doesn't quite see how Jeremy Piven, Adrian Grenier, Hugh Laurie and David Boreanaz are the greatest things since sliced cheese.  Jeez just look at them!  Rawr!

Once you've been tagged, you have to write a blog with six random facts about yourself. In the end you need to choose six people to be tagged and list their names. 

Hmm...let's see... 

1. I'm a packrat and a horrible housekeeper. 

2. I have an insatiable love of grape juice. I can drink it until it makes me sick and yet still want more. 

3. Same with Chinese food, see above. 

4. I'm a pretty good cook, but I hate to do it because I hate to clean up. My grandpa taught me most of what I know, the rest I learned from cookbooks. 

5. I have a thing for older men. Ironically my hubby is my age. 

6. My toes are bright orange and lovely.

Don't know anyone on LJ to tag, so if you want it, have at it.  Let me know in my comments if you do it so I can come read!

One icon, I haven't posted for Pride & Prejudice. I still haven't finished the Colin Firth version, too wrapped up in Entourage at the mo (trying to catch up) but will get back to it soon!
